Subject: @{b}Re: Memorylocation reference question + Intuifont incbining@{ub}

The 13-Mar-01, Torgeir Amundsen wrote:

> when using reference to a memorylocation ?beginfile, ?endoffile etc, i was
> wondering if it's possible to do this in a way using variables, so you can
> use a for-next sentence instead of writing this over and over for dozens
> of files. ?

Do you want to include a huge number of files via a for-loop when you
program is running? If so it is not possible because the call to Incbin is
done by the compiler upon compile-time, not during run-time.

If you want to get hold of the adresses of the included files you could use
a macro, check the example attached.

> Also I want to incbin intuifonts and write these to ram: and then load
> them, but the loading command seems to only read in the fonts: dir. Is
> there any way to get around this?

You could do something like:

  cmd.s= "Assign Fonts: Ram: ADD"
  Execute_ cmd,0,0

and have your fontfile copied there, at the end of your program or when
the font has been read you could remove your added assign in a similar way
if you feel like it :)

//Thor
